	heroObjectPosition={`center center`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you are incarcerated — or you love someone who is — the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> Behind the sentence and the label is a person God still calls His own. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> from beginning to end. Whether you searched "Bible verses for prisoners," "hope in prison," "verses for inmates' families," or "does God still love me" — the answer is the same: no wall can keep out the Father's love. You are not your worst day and you are not your sentence. You are still His, and He has not forgotten you.`}
	keyTakeaway={`You are not your worst day or your sentence — you are still the Father's beloved child, and He has not forgotten you, no matter where you are.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight the incarcerated and their families carry`}
	painsIntroHtml={`Prison is rarely just one person's sentence — it reaches the family at home, the children left behind, and the person trying to come back. If you feel labeled, separated, or forgotten, you are not alone. The numbers say it out loud.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: `1.9M`, label: `people are incarcerated in U.S. prisons and jails on any given day (Prison Policy Initiative, 2024)` },
		{ value: `5.7M`, label: `U.S. children have had a parent incarcerated at some point in their lives (Annie E. Casey Foundation)` },
		{ value: `~68%`, label: `of people released from state prison are rearrested within three years (Bureau of Justice Statistics)` },
		{ value: `27%`, label: `unemployment rate among formerly incarcerated people — higher than the total U.S. rate during any historical period (Prison Policy Initiative)` },
		{ value: `1 in 3`, label: `U.S. adults has a criminal record, a label that follows people long after a sentence ends (The Sentencing Project)` },
		{ value: `~37%`, label: `of people in state prisons have a diagnosed mental health condition (Bureau of Justice Statistics)` },
	]}
	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind every number is a real person — maybe you, maybe someone you love. The shame of a label that follows your name long after the sentence is served. The ache of a phone call that ends too soon. The child counting visits. The fear of coming home to a world that moved on without you, and the quiet worry that even the church has forgotten you.</p><p>None of it means you are beyond reach. It means you're carrying a weight no one was built to carry alone — separation, lost identity, guilt, and the fear of what's next. There is a Father who sees the real person underneath the case number, and He has something to say about who you still are.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
		{ label: `Prison Policy Initiative — Mass Incarceration: The Whole Pie`, url: `https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2024.html` },
		{ label: `Bureau of Justice Statistics`, url: `https://bjs.ojp.gov/` },
		{ label: `The Sentencing Project — Research and Resources`, url: `https://www.sentencingproject.org/research/` },
	]}
	aFatherHeading={`A Father for the incarcerated`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here's what a prison cell can never tell you: the answer to where you are is not a permanent label, a parole date, or finally proving you've changed. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a perfect, holy Father whose love does not stop at any gate, any wall, or any record.</p><p>He is not a warden keeping count of your failures. He is a Father who runs toward His children. He doesn't define you by your worst day, and He doesn't measure you by what society decided you are. He calls you His own — not the future you, not the cleaned-up you, but <em>you</em>, right now, exactly where you are.</p><p>So before you are an inmate, a number, a record, a name people whisper — you are His. Your heavenly Father wants to be the steady voice that says: I see you, I have not forgotten you, and there is no wall high enough to keep My love away from you.</p>`}
