	voiceHeading={`Bible verses for the incarcerated: the Father's voice`}
	voiceIntroHtml={`Nine Bible verses for the incarcerated and their families in the Father's Heart Bible™ — each one a word from your perfect Father about freedom, being remembered, and never being forsaken. Tap any reference to read and listen free.`}
	verses={[
		{ ref: `Psalm 146:7`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 146, text: `Your Father brings justice to the oppressed and gives bread to the hungry; your Father sets the prisoners free.`, note: `The God you're reading about makes a habit of setting prisoners free — it's who your Father is.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 61:1`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 61, text: `The Spirit of the Lord is upon me, for He has anointed me to bring good news to the poor, to bind up the brokenhearted, to proclaim freedom for the captives and release for the prisoners.`, note: `Freedom for captives isn't an afterthought — it's the heart of what your Father came to do.` },
		{ ref: `Hebrews 13:3`, slug: `hebrews`, ch: 13, text: `Remember those in prison as if you were there with them, and those who are mistreated as if you felt it in your own body.`, note: `God commands His people to remember the incarcerated — you are not forgotten by your Father or meant to be by His church.` },
		{ ref: `2 Corinthians 5:17`, slug: `2-corinthians`, ch: 5, text: `If anyone is in Christ, they are a new creation — the old has gone, the new has come.`, note: `Your record is not your future. In your Father's hands, the old is gone and something new begins.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 142:7`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 142, text: `Bring my soul out of prison, that I may praise Your name; the righteous will gather around me, for You have been good to me.`, note: `Written from a cave by a man on the run — your Father hears the cry from confinement and answers it.` },
		{ ref: `John 8:36`, slug: `john`, ch: 8, text: `So if the Son sets you free, you will be free indeed.`, note: `There's a freedom that begins in the heart before the doors ever open — and it's real freedom.` },
		{ ref: `Romans 8:38-39`, slug: `romans`, ch: 8, text: `Nothing — not your past, not your sentence, not anything in all creation — can separate you from the love of your Father.`, note: `No conviction, no wall, no label can cut you off from how much your Father loves you. Nothing.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 139:7-10`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 139, text: `Where can I go from Your Spirit? If I make my bed in the depths, You are there. Even there Your hand will guide me, and Your right hand will hold me fast.`, note: `There is no cell, no depth, no distance where your Father is not already holding you.` },
		{ ref: `Luke 4:18`, slug: `luke`, ch: 4, text: `He has sent me to proclaim freedom for the prisoners and recovery of sight for the blind, to set the oppressed free.`, note: `When Jesus announced His mission, freeing prisoners was at the very center of it.` },
	]}
	offersHeading={`What "our Father" offers you`}
	offersIntroHtml={`Prison strips so much away — freedom, identity, dignity, hope. Here's what your Father gives back, for free, because you are still His.`}
	offersBlocks={[
		{ heading: `A freedom that starts in the heart`, bodyHtml: `Real freedom can begin long before the doors do: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/john/8" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">when the Son sets you free</a>, you are free indeed — free on the inside, today.` },
		{ heading: `A clean start, not a permanent label`, bodyHtml: `Your record is not your verdict. <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/2-corinthians/5" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">In your Father's hands you become a new creation</a> — the old gone, the new begun.` },
		{ heading: `A Father who has not forgotten you`, bodyHtml: `You are not out of sight or out of mind: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/psalms/139" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">there is no cell where He is not already there</a>, holding you fast.` },
		{ heading: `A love nothing can separate you from`, bodyHtml: `Not your past, not your sentence, not the worst thing you've done — <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/romans/8" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">nothing can separate you</a> from your Father's love.` },
	]}
	whyHeading={`Why the Father's Heart Bible™ for the incarcerated`}
	whyBlocks={[
		{ heading: `You meet God as a Father, not a warden`, bodyHtml: `When you've been judged and labeled, the last thing you need is another voice keeping score. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a <em>Father</em> wherever Scripture does — from <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/genesis/1" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Genesis 1</a> on — a Father whose love reaches through any wall, not a warden waiting for you to fail again.` },
		{ heading: `It's free to read and to hear`, bodyHtml: `No account, no purchase, no cost. <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Read it free online</a> with audio on every chapter — many can reach it on facility tablets or once they're home, and families on the outside can read along together, so the Word ties you back to the people you love.` },
		{ heading: `It speaks to the shame and the fear`, bodyHtml: `Carrying guilt, dreading reentry, wondering if you matter? Start with our <a href="/verses/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">verses by topic</a> on forgiveness and hope, or learn to talk to Him with our <a href="/guides/how-to-pray/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">how-to-pray guide</a> — the Word meets you right where you are.` },
	]}
	voicesHeading={`The Father's heart, in their words`}
	voicesIntroHtml={`No wall can keep out the Father's love. The truth beneath every verse here, that God is before anything else a Father who has not forgotten you, is the one these voices gave their lives to:`}
	voices={[
		{ quote: `There is heaven in the depth of that word — Father.`, name: `Charles Spurgeon`, role: `the “Prince of Preachers”`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/e48a128da123135241be9c95cf35b37498d94ea5-500x617.jpg` },
		{ quote: `Answered prayer is the interchange of love between the Father and His child.`, name: `Andrew Murray`, role: `who taught a generation to live as the Father's children`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/133bc45cfa954cf1ae99b7afac5954eca764ed70-500x830.jpg` },
		{ quote: `The hardest, gladdest thing in the world is, to cry Father! from a full heart.`, name: `George MacDonald`, role: `who taught that the Fatherhood of God is the heart of the gospel`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/35e71c2610893383d20b60883aa0b1d4d4664cbc-500x726.jpg` },
	]}
	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; Charles Spurgeon, Andrew Murray, and George MacDonald (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You may not feel free the first time you read it. That's okay. The Father's love isn't a passing feeling — it's a foundation, and foundations get built quietly, one day at a time. Every verse you take in is your Father planting something in you that no wall and no label can uproot.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I have not forgotten you. I know exactly where you are, and there is no wall, no record, and no distance that can keep My love from reaching you. You are not your worst day, and you are not your sentence — you are Mine, and you always have been.</p><p>I am not standing back, counting your failures. I am near, closer than the bars, closer than the shame. When the world labels you and even the people you love feel far away, hear Me: I am your Father, I delight in you still, and I am setting your heart free today — long before any door opens. Come to Me. There is a new beginning in My hands with your name on it."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for the incarcerated and their families`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we lift up everyone behind these walls — every person carrying a label, a sentence, and a weight no one was made to carry alone. Let them hear Your voice above the shame and the noise: that they are not forgotten, not beyond reach, and not defined by their worst day. Reach through every wall with Your love and set their hearts free, even now.</p><p>Father, we pray for the families on the outside — the spouses, the parents, the children counting the days. Comfort them, protect them, and hold the family together across every mile. Give the children a sense of Your nearness when a parent cannot be there, and let no one feel abandoned by You or by Your church.</p><p>We pray for all who are returning home. Go before them into reentry — open doors for work, for housing, for restored relationships and renewed purpose. Guard them from despair, from the pull back toward the old life, and from the lie that they are beyond a new beginning. Make them new creations in You, and let dignity, hope, and restoration follow them every step of the way.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
